-- U.S. Treasury Says Weak European Economy Was Main G-20 Topic
-- B y   K a s i a   K l i m a s i n s k a   a n d   M e e r a   L o u i s
-- 2013-04-19T20:18:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-19/u-s-treasury-says-weak-european-economy-was-main-g-20-topic.html
The euro area’s weak economy was
the main topic of discussion at the Group of 20 meeting today, a
U.S. Treasury Department official said.  The bloc needs to speed up its move toward a more unified
banking system, the official told reporters in  Washington . The
official also said there was a discussion about  Japan ’s monetary
policy and on ensuring those efforts are focused on domestic
demand and not for competitive purposes.  To contact the reporters on this story:
